Week 2 Tutorial

First we reviewed how to load in pet data into R, and to summarize and visualize

# Input pet data 
pets <- c(0,0,1,2,3,3)

# Next summarize pet data
mean(pets)
## [1] 1.5
median(pets)
## [1] 1.5
range(pets)
## [1] 0 3
min(pets)
## [1] 0
max(pets)
## [1] 3
summary(pets)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##    0.00    0.25    1.50    1.50    2.75    3.00
# Visualize Pets 
hist(pets)

hist(pets, 6)

hist(pets)

We then learned how to load data into R, view the first several rows and visualize a variable. (Note that the path here will be different from what we had in class)

# We are going to load the pokemon dataset into R 
pok <- read.csv('datasets/pokemon.csv')

# Observe the first 3 rows of the pokemon dataset
head(pok, 3)
# Select pokemon height 
height <- pok$height_m

# Visualize pokemon heights
hist(height)
